Date: 2019-01-05 18:11
Title: tons of updates, more coming‚Ä¶ (hope I didn‚Äôt break anything ‚ò∫)

<p>I‚Äôve updated a lot of things in MirBSD and for use with the
 Debian operating system. More to come, pax(1) has been converted
 to Mirtoconf (the successful <tt>Build.sh</tt> system of <a
 href="@@@@RELPATH@@@@mksh.htm">mksh</a>‚Äôs) but needs to be re-ported
 to a lot of systems (and some more bugs squished). My <a
 href="https://www.mirbsd.org/~tg/Debs/debidx.htm">‚ÄúWTF‚Äù APT
 repository</a> also received a number of updates, such as to the
 ever-desired wtf(1), but it‚Äôs the time of that two-year cycle
 which invites general care for all of one‚Äôs packages.</p>
<p>On the other hand, MirBSD stops offering RSS feeds by tags.
 The world has become more insular, first by DSGVO, now by other
 cultural issues. I‚Äôll be at FOSDEM, as usual, though, so rejoice!</p>
<p>You can now directly download, for all platforms and synthesisers, <a
 href="https://people.debian.org/~tg/sf/">the soundfonts shipped in
 Debian</a> for MuseScore (and others) I maintain. This service may
 cease at any time, without notice. Also, do mind the MIT licence.</p>
<p>On an unrelated note, happy new year in the western calendar!</p>
